codex
I applied one narrow improvement aimed at the main failure mode from the latest native run: vague decision/reference prompts that should classify as `CLARIFICATION` were collapsing into `DIRECT_ANSWER`.

I added a small seed-side set of clarification exemplars around ambiguous prompts like affordability, choosing, â€œwalk me through this,â€ â€œwould that work,â€ and â€œwhat should I do next here?â€, then regenerated the processed train/validation datasets and SFT JSONL so the next training run will consume the updated supervision. I did not change model architecture, loss shaping, or output formatting.

Files changed:
- `data/raw/v1_seed_dataset.json`
- `data/processed/full_dataset.json`
- `data/processed/preparation_report.json`
- `data/processed/train.json`
- `data/processed/train_sft.jsonl`
- `data/processed/validation.json`
- `data/processed/validation_sft.jsonl`

AUTOMATION_DECISION: CONTINUE
